Up through the rabbit hole
and 'round the big tree.
Down through the rabbit hole,
and then...off goes he?
And there ya have it, lad!\nTyin' a proper bowline knot is\neasy as followin' a rhyme.
Rrrr! My knot is a big old mess.\nI'll never get my stupid tent up!
Here, let me help you with that, Lowen.\nYou just need to put this through here,\naaand... Voila! All done.
Whoa, you've already got this down?\nYou're amazing, Elias!
Oh, it's not so big a deal.\nI just followed the rhyme.
(I can't believe I'm actually camping.\nIt's not exactly my idea of a good time,\nbut I may as well make the most of it.)
(I'll follow along and do what I can to\nhelp. Lowen's a nice enough kid, after all.)
Oh, and if you need more help, just let\nme know. I'm happy to play the role of\nthe wise older brother.
Nya ha ha! The tents are looking good!
If you've finished putting up your tents,\nI'll teach you how to make a fire.
That would be great. Let's go, Lowen!
Okay, first you spin your stick around like\na drill until you start to see smoke.
...Ow! Oof, I skinned my hand good.\nHow's it going for you, Lowen?
I skinned my hand, too—and I don't have\neven a puff of smoke to show for it.
Lighting fires is a test of perseverance.\nOnly those with the tenacity to see it\nthrough will earn the flame.
All right, Lowen, let's keep at—
Already? That's impressive for a first try.
I just borrowed the power of wind\nso I could spin the stick faster!
You really think so? Heh... Thanks.
(Well, I guess he beat me fair and square.\nBut this task was right up Lowen's alley.\nI'll show him next time!)
I'll watch the fire here, boys.\nWhy don't you go help Rex?
We'd be happy to. Come along, Lowen.
Hmm. Last time we came here, we got\nwater from a spring, but she seems to\nhave up'n vanished on us. Must'a run dry.
I guess we'll have to search\nfor a new water source.
But what if we can't find one?!\nWe'll get SO thirsty, and we won't\nbe able to cook anything either.
Now now, such thoughts will get you\nnowhere. You must have faith.
Y-you're right, Elias.\nThis is no time to mope!
(Despite what I just said, finding water\non a mountain isn't going to be easy.)
Oh, a breeze! Does that mean...?\nHere, come this way!
Well, I'll be skinned—ya went'n found\na little rivulet runnin' through these\nhere rocks! Nice goin', Lowen.
I felt a little moisture in the wind blowing\nfrom this direction, so I thought it might\nlead us to water.
Once again, you've come through when\nit matters most, Lowen. Well done.
(Rrrrr! This is NOT looking good for me!)
(I'm older than Lowen! I need to prove\nto him that I'M the capable one!)
Let's get to foraging, boys!\nOtherwise, we're going to bed\nhungry, and I do NOT want that.
Why don't we see which of us can\ngather the most food, Lowen?
And I can be the judge.\nReady? Set? GOOOO!
Nya ha ha! All right, let's see who our\nwinner is and then get to eating!
I picked nuts and berries, and also found\nsome edible vegetables.
Ooo, that's a LOT! I should have known\nyou'd be great at this, Elias.
Looks like I've hit my stride.
As much as I hate to wipe smug looks\noff people's faces, you DO realize all\nthis stuff is poisonous, yeah?
Right then! Let's see if Lowen found\nanything that won't make us keel over.
(Why did I have to make a competition\nout of this? If only we'd gone together...)
Lowen, that's a rainbow truffle!\nIt's the delicacy of delicacies!
Really? Huh. I just found it because\nGaruda taught me how once.
My granny used to say that these truffles\nare so rich, you can make a hundred bowls\nof soup from a single one!
Yay! No one's going hungry tonight.
The truffle soup is almost ready—and\ngood thing, because I am STARVING.
Tomorrow, I'll lead ya lads up the\nmountain and... Hmm? Where'd Elias go?
He was here just a minute ago.\nMaybe he went for a moonlight stroll?
*sigh* Could I have BEEN more pathetic?
Elias! Hey, there you are!\nDinner's almost ready.
Besides, it's not like I had any part of it.\nI didn't make the fire, or find the water,\nOR pick some kind of magic truffle.
Yeah, but I wouldn't have been able\nto do ANY of that stuff without you.
Ever since we got here,\nyou've been looking after me.
That's why I was working so hard—\nI wanted to impress you!
(Is that how Lowen sees me?\nAs some kind of...mentor?)
(But all I cared about was trying\nto show off how skilled I was.)
...You know what, Lowen? I think I WILL\nhave some soup. After all, I'm going to\nneed a lot of energy for tomorrow.
You did great work today, and it makes\nme want to try even harder.
Oh hey, look at the stars!\nThere's soooo many!
Maybe we can find a shooting star.
If we DO see a shooting star,\nwhat are you gonna wish for?
Hmm. Well, there's a lot of things that\nwould make sense, but I think...
Well, I suppose I'd wish to become\nsomeone worthy of respect.
